Package: rustyINLA
Title: Rust Backend for a Focused INLA-Compatible Modeling Subset
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits a focused, INLA-style subset of latent Gaussian models
    through an R formula interface backed by a Rust implementation. The
    current supported surface includes Gaussian, Poisson, Gamma,
    zero-inflated Poisson, and experimental Tweedie likelihoods together
    with iid, rw1, rw2, and ar1 latent effects.
License: `use_mit_license()`, `use_gpl3_license()` or friends to pick a
    license
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Config/rextendr/version: 0.4.2
SystemRequirements: Cargo (Rust's package manager), rustc >= 1.65.0, xz
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.2)
Imports:
    stats,
    utils
